title: MASH 12pc Studio Pro Makeup Make Up Cosmetic Brush Set Kit w/ Leather Case - For Eye Shadow, Blush, Concealer, Etc
description: New from MASH! This 12pc set includes all the brushes you'll ever need to create perfectly polished makeup styles. Perfect for professional salons or personal use! Each brush is covered with a clear plastic wrap for cleanliness. For best result it is recommended to wash brushes & air dry before use. This affordable makeup brushes set contains every brush pictured.How to Clean Makeup Brushes:1. Run the bristles of brush under warm running water.2. Apply a small amount of gentle shampoo to bristles and work into a light lather.3. Rinse bristles thoroughly under running water. You will notice that the water leaving the brush is tinted from old makeup.4. Continue rinsing until no color leaves the brush.5. Allow it to air-dry.

title: BMC Mix Design DIY 3D Silicone Nail Art Decortive Acrylic Cabochon Mold Kit - Set 4, 30pc Kit 1
description: Get your DIY juices flowing! b.m.c happily offer you an outstanding deal on sets of cabochan molds. These 10 piece and 30 piece sets will give a load of design ideas to take your nail art to the next level. All molds are made from a clear silicone to make it easy to remove your acrylic cabochons without damaging them and comes with these designs: Set 1 - Hearts, Candies, Lollipops, Strawberries, Ice Cream Cones, Donuts and Chocolate Bars. Set 2 - Stars, Crosses, Music Notes, Sexy Rabbits, Vintage Sillouhette, Skulls and Crossbones, Letters, Roses, Achors, Hearts, Diamonds, Clubs and Spades. Set 3 - Lots of Flowers, Sealife, Seashells, Leaves, Butterflies, Moons and Stars. Set 4 is a master collection of all molds from sets 1, 2, and 3. Never find yourself with out the most tendiest nails once your start rocking these do-it-yourself cabochon molds. *NOTE*: These sets do not come with acrylic powder and activator to make the cabochons. Visit your local beauty supply/drug store for these supplies. *INSTRUCTIONS*: Pick color(s) acrylic powder and liquid acrylic. With a brush, dip into liquid acrylic and then into your acrylic powder to scoop up some powder. Place acrylic into your desired mold and make sure the mold is completely filled. With your brush, pat down the acrylic to make sure it fully emcompasses the mold. Use liquid acrylic to remove any excess acrylic around the mold and swipe over mold to make sure you have a smooth surface. Let rest for a few minutes if you want a flexible design or put in UV light to completely harden. *DISCLAIMER*: Due to differences between monitor displays, actual color may vary slightly from image. b.m.c is a registered trademark of Remi Collections LLC and is exclusively distributed by Bundle Monster.
